The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the Fourth Annual National Advocacy Summit and Solidarity Dinner for In Defense of Christians. He emphasized that American leadership is crucial to securing the future of Christians in the Middle East and protecting all who are persecuted globally. He spoke about the unprecedented assault on Christianity in the region and the need to confront radical Islamic terrorism. Pence highlighted the efforts of the Trump administration to fight ISIS and provide aid and support to persecuted communities. He also criticized the United Nations for ineffective relief efforts and announced that the United States will provide support directly to persecuted communities through USAID. Pence expressed his faith in the resilience of the Christian communities in the Middle East and their ability to flourish once again.